The paper presents a new differentiable planning module built on Value Iteration, which can be trained using reinforcement learning to solve unseen tasks, generalize to larger map sizes, and navigate in dynamic environments. These tasks involve interactive navigation problems, which are typically addressed in the fields of robotics (cs.RO), computer vision (cs.CV), and control systems (cs.SY). The use of reinforcement learning and deep learning techniques to train the module suggests that it belongs to the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
